<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="334" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="55.[187,1394,3296,3494]" lastBlockId="55.[2076,2669,302,729]" pageId="55" pageNumber="334">
In the past, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Severtzov" authorityYear="1879" box="[364,527,3375,3408]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Arvicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="juldaschi">M. juldaschi</taxonomicName>
was placed in 
<taxonomicName box="[740,836,3375,3408]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Neodon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Neodon</taxonomicName>
, but recent phylogenetic studies based on mtDNA classified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Severtzov" authorityYear="1879" box="[484,605,3414,3447]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Arvicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="juldaschi">juldaschi</taxonomicName>
in subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Argyropulo" authorityYear="1933" box="[791,958,3414,3447]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Blanfordimys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Blanfordimys</taxonomicName>
assister species to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Thomas" baseAuthorityYear="1912" box="[1228,1394,3414,3447]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Microtus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="332" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="afghanus">M. afghanus</taxonomicName>
and M. bucharensis. In the past, carruthersi was considered a separate species; hybrids between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Severtzov" authorityYear="1879" box="[2206,2326,302,335]" class="Mammalia" family="Cricetidae" genus="Arvicola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="juldaschi">juldaschi</taxonomicName>
and carruthersi are fertile. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="55" pageNumber="334" type="synonymic_list">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6760547" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6760547" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6760547/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="55" pageNumber="334" startId="55.[2076,2230,385,414]" targetBox="[1461,2052,310,724]" targetPageId="55">
<paragraph blockId="55.[2076,2669,302,729]" box="[2076,2477,385,414]" pageId="55" pageNumber="334">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[2076,2477,385,414]" pageId="55" pageNumber="334">Subspecies and Distribution.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
